27 // Used to build addressing modes. ----
28 struct SystemZAddressingMode { ----
29 // The shape of the address. ----
30 enum AddrForm { ----
31 // base+displacement ----
32 FormBD, ----
33 ----
34 // base+displacement+index for load and store operands ----
35 FormBDXNormal, ----
36 ----
37 // base+displacement+index for load address operands ----
38 FormBDXLA, ----
39 ----
40 // base+displacement+index+ADJDYNALLOC ----
41 FormBDXDynAlloc ----
42 }; ----
43 AddrForm Form; ----
44 ----
45 // The type of displacement. The enum names here correspond directly ----
46 // to the definitions in SystemZOperand.td. We could split them into ----
47 // flags -- single/pair, 128-bit, etc. -- but it hardly seems worth it. ----
48 enum DispRange { ----
49 Disp12Only, ----
50 Disp12Pair, ----
51 Disp20Only, ----
52 Disp20Only128, ----
53 Disp20Pair ----
54 }; ----
55 DispRange DR; ----
56 ----
57 // The parts of the address. The address is equivalent to: ----
58 // ----
59 // Base + Disp + Index + (IncludesDynAlloc ? ADJDYNALLOC : 0) ----
60 SDValue Base; ----
61 int64_t Disp; ----
62 SDValue Index; ----
63 bool IncludesDynAlloc; ----
64 ----
65 SystemZAddressingMode(AddrForm form, DispRange dr) 0
66 : Form(form), DR(dr), Disp(0), IncludesDynAlloc(false) {} 0
67 ----
68 // True if the address can have an index register. ----
69 bool hasIndexField() { return Form != FormBD; } 0
70 ----
71 // True if the address can (and must) include ADJDYNALLOC. ----
72 bool isDynAlloc() { return Form == FormBDXDynAlloc; } 0
73 ----
74 void dump(const llvm::SelectionDAG *DAG) { 0
75 errs() << "SystemZAddressingMode " << this << '\n'; 0
76 ----
77 errs() << " Base "; 0
78 if (Base.getNode()) 0
79 Base.getNode()->dump(DAG); 0
80 else ----
81 errs() << "null\n"; 0
82 ----
83 if (hasIndexField()) { 0
84 errs() << " Index "; 0
85 if (Index.getNode()) 0
86 Index.getNode()->dump(DAG); 0
87 else ----
88 errs() << "null\n"; 0
89 } ----
90 ----
91 errs() << " Disp " << Disp; 0
92 if (IncludesDynAlloc) 0
93 errs() << " + ADJDYNALLOC"; 0
94 errs() << '\n'; 0
95 } 0
96 }; ----

98 // Return a mask with Count low bits set. ----
99 static uint64_t allOnes(unsigned int Count) { 0
100 assert(Count <= 64); 0
101 if (Count > 63) 0
102 return UINT64_MAX; 0
103 return (uint64_t(1) << Count) - 1; 0
104 } ----
105 ----
106 // Represents operands 2 to 5 of the ROTATE AND ... SELECTED BITS operation ----
107 // given by Opcode. The operands are: Input (R2), Start (I3), End (I4) and ----
108 // Rotate (I5). The combined operand value is effectively: ----
109 // ----
110 // (or (rotl Input, Rotate), ~Mask) ----
111 // ----
112 // for RNSBG and: ----
113 // ----
114 // (and (rotl Input, Rotate), Mask) ----
115 // ----
116 // otherwise. The output value has BitSize bits, although Input may be ----
117 // narrower (in which case the upper bits are don't care), or wider (in which ----
118 // case the result will be truncated as part of the operation). ----
119 struct RxSBGOperands { ----
120 RxSBGOperands(unsigned Op, SDValue N) 0
121 : Opcode(Op), BitSize(N.getValueSizeInBits()), 0
122 Mask(allOnes(BitSize)), Input(N), Start(64 - BitSize), End(63), 0
123 Rotate(0) {} 0
124 ----
125 unsigned Opcode; ----
126 unsigned BitSize; ----
127 uint64_t Mask; ----
128 SDValue Input; ----
129 unsigned Start; ----
130 unsigned End; ----
131 unsigned Rotate; ----
132 }; ----

321 // Return true if Load and Store are loads and stores of the same size ----
322 // and are guaranteed not to overlap. Such operations can be implemented ----
323 // using block (SS-format) instructions. ----
324 // ----
325 // Partial overlap would lead to incorrect code, since the block operations ----
326 // are logically bytewise, even though they have a fast path for the ----
327 // non-overlapping case. We also need to avoid full overlap (i.e. two ----
328 // addresses that might be equal at run time) because although that case ----
329 // would be handled correctly, it might be implemented by millicode. ----

390 // Return true if Val should be selected as a displacement for an address ----
391 // with range DR. Here we're interested in the range of both the instruction ----
392 // described by DR and of any pairing instruction. ----
393 static bool selectDisp(SystemZAddressingMode::DispRange DR, int64_t Val) { 0
394 switch (DR) { 0
395 case SystemZAddressingMode::Disp12Only: 0
396 return isUInt<12>(Val); 0
397 ----
398 case SystemZAddressingMode::Disp12Pair: 0
399 case SystemZAddressingMode::Disp20Only: ----
400 case SystemZAddressingMode::Disp20Pair: ----
401 return isInt<20>(Val); 0
402 ----
403 case SystemZAddressingMode::Disp20Only128: 0
404 return isInt<20>(Val) && isInt<20>(Val + 8); 0
405 } ----
406 llvm_unreachable("Unhandled displacement range"); 0
407 } ----

409 // Change the base or index in AM to Value, where IsBase selects ----
410 // between the base and index. ----
411 static void changeComponent(SystemZAddressingMode &AM, bool IsBase, 0
412 SDValue Value) { ----
413 if (IsBase) 0
414 AM.Base = Value; 0
415 else ----
416 AM.Index = Value; 0
417 } 0
418 ----
419 // The base or index of AM is equivalent to Value + ADJDYNALLOC, ----
420 // where IsBase selects between the base and index. Try to fold the ----
421 // ADJDYNALLOC into AM. ----
422 static bool expandAdjDynAlloc(SystemZAddressingMode &AM, bool IsBase, 0
423 SDValue Value) { ----
424 if (AM.isDynAlloc() && !AM.IncludesDynAlloc) { 0
425 changeComponent(AM, IsBase, Value); 0
426 AM.IncludesDynAlloc = true; 0
427 return true; 0
428 } ----
429 return false; 0
430 } ----
431 ----
432 // The base of AM is equivalent to Base + Index. Try to use Index as ----
433 // the index register. ----
434 static bool expandIndex(SystemZAddressingMode &AM, SDValue Base, 0
435 SDValue Index) { ----
436 if (AM.hasIndexField() && !AM.Index.getNode()) { 0
437 AM.Base = Base; 0
438 AM.Index = Index; 0
439 return true; 0
440 } ----
441 return false; 0
442 } ----
443 ----
444 // The base or index of AM is equivalent to Op0 + Op1, where IsBase selects ----
445 // between the base and index. Try to fold Op1 into AM's displacement. ----
446 static bool expandDisp(SystemZAddressingMode &AM, bool IsBase, 0
447 SDValue Op0, uint64_t Op1) { ----
448 // First try adjusting the displacement. ----
449 int64_t TestDisp = AM.Disp + Op1; 0
450 if (selectDisp(AM.DR, TestDisp)) { 0
451 changeComponent(AM, IsBase, Op0); 0
452 AM.Disp = TestDisp; 0
453 return true; 0
454 } ----
455 ----
456 // We could consider forcing the displacement into a register and ----
457 // using it as an index, but it would need to be carefully tuned. ----
458 return false; 0
459 } ----
460 ----
461 bool SystemZDAGToDAGISel::expandAddress(SystemZAddressingMode &AM, 0
462 bool IsBase) const { ----
463 SDValue N = IsBase ? AM.Base : AM.Index; 0
464 unsigned Opcode = N.getOpcode(); 0
465 if (Opcode == ISD::TRUNCATE) { 0
466 N = N.getOperand(0); 0
467 Opcode = N.getOpcode(); 0
468 } ----
469 if (Opcode == ISD::ADD || CurDAG->isBaseWithConstantOffset(N)) { 0
470 SDValue Op0 = N.getOperand(0); 0
471 SDValue Op1 = N.getOperand(1); 0
472 ----
473 unsigned Op0Code = Op0->getOpcode(); 0
474 unsigned Op1Code = Op1->getOpcode(); 0
475 ----
476 if (Op0Code == SystemZISD::ADJDYNALLOC) 0
477 return expandAdjDynAlloc(AM, IsBase, Op1); 0
478 if (Op1Code == SystemZISD::ADJDYNALLOC) 0
479 return expandAdjDynAlloc(AM, IsBase, Op0); 0
480 ----
481 if (Op0Code == ISD::Constant) 0
482 return expandDisp(AM, IsBase, Op1, 0
483 cast(Op0)->getSExtValue()); 0
484 if (Op1Code == ISD::Constant) 0
485 return expandDisp(AM, IsBase, Op0, 0
486 cast(Op1)->getSExtValue()); 0
487 ----
488 if (IsBase && expandIndex(AM, Op0, Op1)) 0
489 return true; 0
490 } ----
491 if (Opcode == SystemZISD::PCREL_OFFSET) { 0
492 SDValue Full = N.getOperand(0); 0
493 SDValue Base = N.getOperand(1); 0
494 SDValue Anchor = Base.getOperand(0); 0
495 uint64_t Offset = (cast(Full)->getOffset() - 0
496 cast(Anchor)->getOffset()); 0
497 return expandDisp(AM, IsBase, Base, Offset); 0
498 } ----
499 return false; 0
500 } ----

502 // Return true if an instruction with displacement range DR should be ----
503 // used for displacement value Val. selectDisp(DR, Val) must already hold. ----
504 static bool isValidDisp(SystemZAddressingMode::DispRange DR, int64_t Val) { 0
505 assert(selectDisp(DR, Val) && "Invalid displacement"); 0
506 switch (DR) { 0
507 case SystemZAddressingMode::Disp12Only: 0
508 case SystemZAddressingMode::Disp20Only: ----
509 case SystemZAddressingMode::Disp20Only128: ----
510 return true; 0
511 ----
512 case SystemZAddressingMode::Disp12Pair: 0
513 // Use the other instruction if the displacement is too large. ----
514 return isUInt<12>(Val); 0
515 ----
516 case SystemZAddressingMode::Disp20Pair: 0
517 // Use the other instruction if the displacement is small enough. ----
518 return !isUInt<12>(Val); 0
519 } ----
520 llvm_unreachable("Unhandled displacement range"); 0
521 } ----
522 ----
523 // Return true if Base + Disp + Index should be performed by LA(Y). ----
524 static bool shouldUseLA(SDNode *Base, int64_t Disp, SDNode *Index) { 0
525 // Don't use LA(Y) for constants. ----
526 if (!Base) 0
527 return false; 0
528 ----
529 // Always use LA(Y) for frame addresses, since we know that the destination ----
530 // register is almost always (perhaps always) going to be different from ----
531 // the frame register. ----
532 if (Base->getOpcode() == ISD::FrameIndex) 0
533 return true; 0
534 ----
535 if (Disp) { 0
536 // Always use LA(Y) if there is a base, displacement and index. ----
537 if (Index) 0
538 return true; 0
539 ----
540 // Always use LA if the displacement is small enough. It should always ----
541 // be no worse than AGHI (and better if it avoids a move). ----
542 if (isUInt<12>(Disp)) 0
543 return true; 0
544 ----
545 // For similar reasons, always use LAY if the constant is too big for AGHI. ----
546 // LAY should be no worse than AGFI. ----
547 if (!isInt<16>(Disp)) 0
548 return true; 0
549 } else { ----
550 // Don't use LA for plain registers. ----
551 if (!Index) 0
552 return false; 0
553 ----
554 // Don't use LA for plain addition if the index operand is only used ----
555 // once. It should be a natural two-operand addition in that case. ----
556 if (Index->hasOneUse()) 0
557 return false; 0
558 ----
559 // Prefer addition if the second operation is sign-extended, in the ----
560 // hope of using AGF. ----
561 unsigned IndexOpcode = Index->getOpcode(); 0
562 if (IndexOpcode == ISD::SIGN_EXTEND || 0
563 IndexOpcode == ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG) ----
564 return false; 0
565 } ----
566 ----
567 // Don't use LA for two-operand addition if either operand is only ----
568 // used once. The addition instructions are better in that case. ----
569 if (Base->hasOneUse()) 0
570 return false; 0
571 ----
572 return true; 0
573 } ----
574 ----
575 // Return true if Addr is suitable for AM, updating AM if so. ----
576 bool SystemZDAGToDAGISel::selectAddress(SDValue Addr, 0
577 SystemZAddressingMode &AM) const { ----
578 // Start out assuming that the address will need to be loaded separately, ----
579 // then try to extend it as much as we can. ----
580 AM.Base = Addr; 0
581 ----
582 // First try treating the address as a constant. ----
583 if (Addr.getOpcode() == ISD::Constant && 0
584 expandDisp(AM, true, SDValue(), 0
585 cast(Addr)->getSExtValue())) 0
586 ; ----
587 // Also see if it's a bare ADJDYNALLOC. ----
588 else if (Addr.getOpcode() == SystemZISD::ADJDYNALLOC && 0
589 expandAdjDynAlloc(AM, true, SDValue())) 0
590 ; ----
591 else ----
592 // Otherwise try expanding each component. ----
593 while (expandAddress(AM, true) || 0
594 (AM.Index.getNode() && expandAddress(AM, false))) 0
595 continue; 0
596 ----
597 // Reject cases where it isn't profitable to use LA(Y). ----
598 if (AM.Form == SystemZAddressingMode::FormBDXLA && 0
599 !shouldUseLA(AM.Base.getNode(), AM.Disp, AM.Index.getNode())) 0
600 return false; 0
601 ----
602 // Reject cases where the other instruction in a pair should be used. ----
603 if (!isValidDisp(AM.DR, AM.Disp)) 0
604 return false; 0
605 ----
606 // Make sure that ADJDYNALLOC is included where necessary. ----
607 if (AM.isDynAlloc() && !AM.IncludesDynAlloc) 0
608 return false; 0
609 ----
610 LLVM_DEBUG(AM.dump(CurDAG)); 0
611 return true; 0
612 } ----
613 ----
614 // Insert a node into the DAG at least before Pos. This will reposition ----
615 // the node as needed, and will assign it a node ID that is <= Pos's ID. ----
616 // Note that this does *not* preserve the uniqueness of node IDs! ----
617 // The selection DAG must no longer depend on their uniqueness when this ----
618 // function is used. ----
619 static void insertDAGNode(SelectionDAG *DAG, SDNode *Pos, SDValue N) { 0
620 if (N->getNodeId() == -1 || 0
621 (SelectionDAGISel::getUninvalidatedNodeId(N.getNode()) > 0
622 SelectionDAGISel::getUninvalidatedNodeId(Pos))) { 0
623 DAG->RepositionNode(Pos->getIterator(), N.getNode()); 0
624 // Mark Node as invalid for pruning as after this it may be a successor to a ----
625 // selected node but otherwise be in the same position of Pos. ----
626 // Conservatively mark it with the same -abs(Id) to assure node id ----
627 // invariant is preserved. ----
628 N->setNodeId(Pos->getNodeId()); 0
629 SelectionDAGISel::InvalidateNodeId(N.getNode()); 0
630 } ----
631 } 0
632 ----
633 void SystemZDAGToDAGISel::getAddressOperands(const SystemZAddressingMode &AM, 0
634 EVT VT, SDValue &Base, ----
635 SDValue &Disp) const { ----
636 Base = AM.Base; 0
637 if (!Base.getNode()) 0
638 // Register 0 means "no base". This is mostly useful for shifts. ----
639 Base = CurDAG->getRegister(0, VT); 0
640 else if (Base.getOpcode() == ISD::FrameIndex) { 0
641 // Lower a FrameIndex to a TargetFrameIndex. ----
642 int64_t FrameIndex = cast(Base)->getIndex(); 0
643 Base = CurDAG->getTargetFrameIndex(FrameIndex, VT); 0
644 } else if (Base.getValueType() != VT) { 0
645 // Truncate values from i64 to i32, for shifts. ----
646 assert(VT == MVT::i32 && Base.getValueType() == MVT::i64 && 0
647 "Unexpected truncation"); ----
648 SDLoc DL(Base); 0
649 SDValue Trunc = CurDAG->getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, VT, Base); 0
650 insertDAGNode(CurDAG, Base.getNode(), Trunc); 0
651 Base = Trunc; 0
652 } 0
653 ----
654 // Lower the displacement to a TargetConstant. ----
655 Disp = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(AM.Disp, SDLoc(Base), VT); 0
656 } 0
657 ----
658 void SystemZDAGToDAGISel::getAddressOperands(const SystemZAddressingMode &AM, 0
659 EVT VT, SDValue &Base, ----
660 SDValue &Disp, ----
661 SDValue &Index) const { ----
662 getAddressOperands(AM, VT, Base, Disp); 0
663 ----
664 Index = AM.Index; 0
665 if (!Index.getNode()) 0
666 // Register 0 means "no index". ----
667 Index = CurDAG->getRegister(0, VT); 0
668 } 0

704 bool SystemZDAGToDAGISel::selectBDVAddr12Only(SDValue Addr, SDValue Elem, 0

709 if (selectBDXAddr12Only(Addr, Regs[0], Disp, Regs[1]) && 0
710 Regs[0].getNode() && Regs[1].getNode()) { 0
711 for (unsigned int I = 0; I < 2; ++I) { 0
712 Base = Regs[I]; 0
713 Index = Regs[1 - I]; 0
714 // We can't tell here whether the index vector has the right type ----
715 // for the access; the caller needs to do that instead. ----
716 if (Index.getOpcode() == ISD::ZERO_EXTEND) 0
717 Index = Index.getOperand(0); 0
718 if (Index.getOpcode() == ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT && 0
719 Index.getOperand(1) == Elem) { 0

721 return true; 0

723 } ----

725 return false; 0

727 ----
728 bool SystemZDAGToDAGISel::detectOrAndInsertion(SDValue &Op, 0
729 uint64_t InsertMask) const { ----
730 // We're only interested in cases where the insertion is into some operand ----
731 // of Op, rather than into Op itself. The only useful case is an AND. ----
732 if (Op.getOpcode() != ISD::AND) 0
733 return false; 0
734 ----
735 // We need a constant mask. ----
736 auto *MaskNode = dyn_cast(Op.getOperand(1).getNode()); 0
737 if (!MaskNode) 0
738 return false; 0
739 ----
740 // It's not an insertion of Op.getOperand(0) if the two masks overlap. ----
741 uint64_t AndMask = MaskNode->getZExtValue(); 0
742 if (InsertMask & AndMask) 0
743 return false; 0
744 ----
745 // It's only an insertion if all bits are covered or are known to be zero. ----
746 // The inner check covers all cases but is more expensive. ----
747 uint64_t Used = allOnes(Op.getValueSizeInBits()); 0
748 if (Used != (AndMask | InsertMask)) { 0
749 KnownBits Known = CurDAG->computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0)); 0
750 if (Used != (AndMask | InsertMask | Known.Zero.getZExtValue())) 0
751 return false; 0
752 } 0
753 ----
754 Op = Op.getOperand(0); 0
755 return true; 0
756 } ----
757 ----
758 bool SystemZDAGToDAGISel::refineRxSBGMask(RxSBGOperands &RxSBG, 0
759 uint64_t Mask) const { ----
760 const SystemZInstrInfo *TII = getInstrInfo(); 0
761 if (RxSBG.Rotate != 0) 0
762 Mask = (Mask << RxSBG.Rotate) | (Mask >> (64 - RxSBG.Rotate)); 0
763 Mask &= RxSBG.Mask; 0
764 if (TII->isRxSBGMask(Mask, RxSBG.BitSize, RxSBG.Start, RxSBG.End)) { 0
765 RxSBG.Mask = Mask; 0
766 return true; 0
767 } ----
768 return false; 0
769 } ----
770 ----
771 // Return true if any bits of (RxSBG.Input & Mask) are significant. ----
772 static bool maskMatters(RxSBGOperands &RxSBG, uint64_t Mask) { 0
773 // Rotate the mask in the same way as RxSBG.Input is rotated. ----
774 if (RxSBG.Rotate != 0) 0
775 Mask = ((Mask << RxSBG.Rotate) | (Mask >> (64 - RxSBG.Rotate))); 0
776 return (Mask & RxSBG.Mask) != 0; 0
777 } ----
778 ----
779 bool SystemZDAGToDAGISel::expandRxSBG(RxSBGOperands &RxSBG) const { 0
780 SDValue N = RxSBG.Input; 0
781 unsigned Opcode = N.getOpcode(); 0
782 switch (Opcode) { 0
783 case ISD::TRUNCATE: { 0
784 if (RxSBG.Opcode == SystemZ::RNSBG) 0
785 return false; 0
786 uint64_t BitSize = N.getValueSizeInBits(); 0
787 uint64_t Mask = allOnes(BitSize); 0
788 if (!refineRxSBGMask(RxSBG, Mask)) 0
789 return false; 0
790 RxSBG.Input = N.getOperand(0); 0
791 return true; 0
792 } ----
793 case ISD::AND: { 0
794 if (RxSBG.Opcode == SystemZ::RNSBG) 0
795 return false; 0
796 ----
797 auto *MaskNode = dyn_cast(N.getOperand(1).getNode()); 0
798 if (!MaskNode) 0
799 return false; 0
800 ----
801 SDValue Input = N.getOperand(0); 0
802 uint64_t Mask = MaskNode->getZExtValue(); 0
803 if (!refineRxSBGMask(RxSBG, Mask)) { 0
804 // If some bits of Input are already known zeros, those bits will have ----
805 // been removed from the mask. See if adding them back in makes the ----
806 // mask suitable. ----
807 KnownBits Known = CurDAG->computeKnownBits(Input); 0
808 Mask |= Known.Zero.getZExtValue(); 0
809 if (!refineRxSBGMask(RxSBG, Mask)) 0
810 return false; 0
811 } 0
812 RxSBG.Input = Input; 0
813 return true; 0
814 } ----
815 ----
816 case ISD::OR: { 0
817 if (RxSBG.Opcode != SystemZ::RNSBG) 0
818 return false; 0
819 ----
820 auto *MaskNode = dyn_cast(N.getOperand(1).getNode()); 0
821 if (!MaskNode) 0
822 return false; 0
823 ----
824 SDValue Input = N.getOperand(0); 0
825 uint64_t Mask = ~MaskNode->getZExtValue(); 0
826 if (!refineRxSBGMask(RxSBG, Mask)) { 0
827 // If some bits of Input are already known ones, those bits will have ----
828 // been removed from the mask. See if adding them back in makes the ----
829 // mask suitable. ----
830 KnownBits Known = CurDAG->computeKnownBits(Input); 0
831 Mask &= ~Known.One.getZExtValue(); 0
832 if (!refineRxSBGMask(RxSBG, Mask)) 0
833 return false; 0
834 } 0
835 RxSBG.Input = Input; 0
836 return true; 0
837 } ----
838 ----
839 case ISD::ROTL: { 0
840 // Any 64-bit rotate left can be merged into the RxSBG. ----
841 if (RxSBG.BitSize != 64 || N.getValueType() != MVT::i64) 0
842 return false; 0
843 auto *CountNode = dyn_cast(N.getOperand(1).getNode()); 0
844 if (!CountNode) 0
845 return false; 0
846 ----
847 RxSBG.Rotate = (RxSBG.Rotate + CountNode->getZExtValue()) & 63; 0
848 RxSBG.Input = N.getOperand(0); 0
849 return true; 0
850 } ----
851 ----
852 case ISD::ANY_EXTEND: 0
853 // Bits above the extended operand are don't-care. ----
854 RxSBG.Input = N.getOperand(0); 0
855 return true; 0
856 ----
857 case ISD::ZERO_EXTEND: 0
858 if (RxSBG.Opcode != SystemZ::RNSBG) { 0
859 // Restrict the mask to the extended operand. ----
860 unsigned InnerBitSize = N.getOperand(0).getValueSizeInBits(); 0
861 if (!refineRxSBGMask(RxSBG, allOnes(InnerBitSize))) 0
862 return false; 0
863 ----
864 RxSBG.Input = N.getOperand(0); 0
865 return true; 0
866 } ----
867 [[fallthrough]]; ----
868 ----
869 case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND: { ----
870 // Check that the extension bits are don't-care (i.e. are masked out ----
871 // by the final mask). ----
872 unsigned BitSize = N.getValueSizeInBits(); 0
873 unsigned InnerBitSize = N.getOperand(0).getValueSizeInBits(); 0
874 if (maskMatters(RxSBG, allOnes(BitSize) - allOnes(InnerBitSize))) { 0
875 // In the case where only the sign bit is active, increase Rotate with ----
876 // the extension width. ----
877 if (RxSBG.Mask == 1 && RxSBG.Rotate == 1) 0
878 RxSBG.Rotate += (BitSize - InnerBitSize); 0
879 else ----
880 return false; 0
881 } ----
882 ----
883 RxSBG.Input = N.getOperand(0); 0
884 return true; 0
885 } ----
886 ----
887 case ISD::SHL: { 0
888 auto *CountNode = dyn_cast(N.getOperand(1).getNode()); 0
889 if (!CountNode) 0
890 return false; 0
891 ----
892 uint64_t Count = CountNode->getZExtValue(); 0
893 unsigned BitSize = N.getValueSizeInBits(); 0
894 if (Count < 1 || Count >= BitSize) 0
895 return false; 0
896 ----
897 if (RxSBG.Opcode == SystemZ::RNSBG) { 0
898 // Treat (shl X, count) as (rotl X, size-count) as long as the bottom ----
899 // count bits from RxSBG.Input are ignored. ----
900 if (maskMatters(RxSBG, allOnes(Count))) 0
901 return false; 0
902 } else { ----
903 // Treat (shl X, count) as (and (rotl X, count), ~0< ----
904 if (!refineRxSBGMask(RxSBG, allOnes(BitSize - Count) << Count)) 0
905 return false; 0
906 } ----
907 ----
908 RxSBG.Rotate = (RxSBG.Rotate + Count) & 63; 0
909 RxSBG.Input = N.getOperand(0); 0
910 return true; 0
911 } ----
912 ----
913 case ISD::SRL: 0
914 case ISD::SRA: { ----
915 auto *CountNode = dyn_cast(N.getOperand(1).getNode()); 0
916 if (!CountNode) 0
917 return false; 0
918 ----
919 uint64_t Count = CountNode->getZExtValue(); 0
920 unsigned BitSize = N.getValueSizeInBits(); 0
921 if (Count < 1 || Count >= BitSize) 0
922 return false; 0
923 ----
924 if (RxSBG.Opcode == SystemZ::RNSBG || Opcode == ISD::SRA) { 0
925 // Treat (srl|sra X, count) as (rotl X, size-count) as long as the top ----
926 // count bits from RxSBG.Input are ignored. ----
927 if (maskMatters(RxSBG, allOnes(Count) << (BitSize - Count))) 0
928 return false; 0
929 } else { ----
930 // Treat (srl X, count), mask) as (and (rotl X, size-count), ~0>>count), ----
931 // which is similar to SLL above. ----
932 if (!refineRxSBGMask(RxSBG, allOnes(BitSize - Count))) 0
933 return false; 0
934 } ----
935 ----
936 RxSBG.Rotate = (RxSBG.Rotate - Count) & 63; 0
937 RxSBG.Input = N.getOperand(0); 0
938 return true; 0
939 } ----
940 default: 0
941 return false; 0
942 } ----
943 } ----
944 ----
945 SDValue SystemZDAGToDAGISel::getUNDEF(const SDLoc &DL, EVT VT) const { 0
946 SDNode *N = CurDAG->getMachineNode(TargetOpcode::IMPLICIT_DEF, DL, VT); 0
947 return SDValue(N, 0); 0
948 } ----
949 ----
950 SDValue SystemZDAGToDAGISel::convertTo(const SDLoc &DL, EVT VT, 0
951 SDValue N) const { ----
952 if (N.getValueType() == MVT::i32 && VT == MVT::i64) 0
953 return CurDAG->getTargetInsertSubreg(SystemZ::subreg_l32, 0
954 DL, VT, getUNDEF(DL, MVT::i64), N); 0
955 if (N.getValueType() == MVT::i64 && VT == MVT::i32) 0
956 return CurDAG->getTargetExtractSubreg(SystemZ::subreg_l32, DL, VT, N); 0
957 assert(N.getValueType() == VT && "Unexpected value types"); 0
958 return N; 0
959 } ----
960 ----
961 bool SystemZDAGToDAGISel::tryRISBGZero(SDNode *N) { 0
962 SDLoc DL(N); 0
963 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0); 0
964 if (!VT.isInteger() || VT.getSizeInBits() > 64) 0
965 return false; 0
966 RxSBGOperands RISBG(SystemZ::RISBG, SDValue(N, 0)); 0
967 unsigned Count = 0; 0
968 while (expandRxSBG(RISBG)) 0
969 // The widening or narrowing is expected to be free. ----
970 // Counting widening or narrowing as a saved operation will result in ----
971 // preferring an R*SBG over a simple shift/logical instruction. ----
972 if (RISBG.Input.getOpcode() != ISD::ANY_EXTEND && 0
973 RISBG.Input.getOpcode() != ISD::TRUNCATE) 0
974 Count += 1; 0
975 if (Count == 0 || isa(RISBG.Input)) 0
976 return false; 0
977 ----
978 // Prefer to use normal shift instructions over RISBG, since they can handle ----
979 // all cases and are sometimes shorter. ----
980 if (Count == 1 && N->getOpcode() != ISD::AND) 0
981 return false; 0
982 ----
983 // Prefer register extensions like LLC over RISBG. Also prefer to start ----
984 // out with normal ANDs if one instruction would be enough. We can convert ----
985 // these ANDs into an RISBG later if a three-address instruction is useful. ----
986 if (RISBG.Rotate == 0) { 0
987 bool PreferAnd = false; 0
988 // Prefer AND for any 32-bit and-immediate operation. ----
989 if (VT == MVT::i32) 0
990 PreferAnd = true; 0
991 // As well as for any 64-bit operation that can be implemented via LLC(R), ----
992 // LLH(R), LLGT(R), or one of the and-immediate instructions. ----
993 else if (RISBG.Mask == 0xff || 0
994 RISBG.Mask == 0xffff || 0
995 RISBG.Mask == 0x7fffffff || 0
996 SystemZ::isImmLF(~RISBG.Mask) || 0
997 SystemZ::isImmHF(~RISBG.Mask)) 0
998 PreferAnd = true; 0
999 // And likewise for the LLZRGF instruction, which doesn't have a register ----
1000 // to register version. ----
1001 else if (auto *Load = dyn_cast(RISBG.Input)) { 0
1002 if (Load->getMemoryVT() == MVT::i32 && 0
1003 (Load->getExtensionType() == ISD::EXTLOAD || 0
1004 Load->getExtensionType() == ISD::ZEXTLOAD) && 0
1005 RISBG.Mask == 0xffffff00 && 0
1006 Subtarget->hasLoadAndZeroRightmostByte()) 0
1007 PreferAnd = true; 0
1008 } ----
1009 if (PreferAnd) { 0
1010 // Replace the current node with an AND. Note that the current node ----
1011 // might already be that same AND, in which case it is already CSE'd ----
1012 // with it, and we must not call ReplaceNode. ----
1013 SDValue In = convertTo(DL, VT, RISBG.Input); 0
1014 SDValue Mask = CurDAG->getConstant(RISBG.Mask, DL, VT); 0
1015 SDValue New = CurDAG->getNode(ISD::AND, DL, VT, In, Mask); 0
1016 if (N != New.getNode()) { 0
1017 insertDAGNode(CurDAG, N, Mask); 0
1018 insertDAGNode(CurDAG, N, New); 0
1019 ReplaceNode(N, New.getNode()); 0
1020 N = New.getNode(); 0
1021 } ----
1022 // Now, select the machine opcode to implement this operation. ----
1023 if (!N->isMachineOpcode()) 0
1024 SelectCode(N); 0
1025 return true; 0
1026 } ----
1027 } ----
1028 ----
1029 unsigned Opcode = SystemZ::RISBG; 0
1030 // Prefer RISBGN if available, since it does not clobber CC. ----
1031 if (Subtarget->hasMiscellaneousExtensions()) 0
1032 Opcode = SystemZ::RISBGN; 0
1033 EVT OpcodeVT = MVT::i64; 0
1034 if (VT == MVT::i32 && Subtarget->hasHighWord() && 0
1035 // We can only use the 32-bit instructions if all source bits are ----
1036 // in the low 32 bits without wrapping, both after rotation (because ----
1037 // of the smaller range for Start and End) and before rotation ----
1038 // (because the input value is truncated). ----
1039 RISBG.Start >= 32 && RISBG.End >= RISBG.Start && 0
1040 ((RISBG.Start + RISBG.Rotate) & 63) >= 32 && 0
1041 ((RISBG.End + RISBG.Rotate) & 63) >= 0
1042 ((RISBG.Start + RISBG.Rotate) & 63)) { 0
1043 Opcode = SystemZ::RISBMux; 0
1044 OpcodeVT = MVT::i32; 0
1045 RISBG.Start &= 31; 0
1046 RISBG.End &= 31; 0
1047 } ----
1048 SDValue Ops[5] = { ----
1049 getUNDEF(DL, OpcodeVT), 0
1050 convertTo(DL, OpcodeVT, RISBG.Input), 0
1051 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(RISBG.Start, DL, MVT::i32), 0
1052 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(RISBG.End | 128, DL, MVT::i32), 0
1053 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(RISBG.Rotate, DL, MVT::i32) 0
1054 }; 0
1055 SDValue New = convertTo( 0
1056 DL, VT, SDValue(CurDAG->getMachineNode(Opcode, DL, OpcodeVT, Ops), 0)); 0
1057 ReplaceNode(N, New.getNode()); 0
1058 return true; 0
1059 } 0
1060 ----
1061 bool SystemZDAGToDAGISel::tryRxSBG(SDNode *N, unsigned Opcode) { 0
1062 SDLoc DL(N); 0
1063 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0); 0
1064 if (!VT.isInteger() || VT.getSizeInBits() > 64) 0
1065 return false; 0
1066 // Try treating each operand of N as the second operand of the RxSBG ----
1067 // and see which goes deepest. ----
1068 RxSBGOperands RxSBG[] = { ----
1069 RxSBGOperands(Opcode, N->getOperand(0)), 0
1070 RxSBGOperands(Opcode, N->getOperand(1)) 0
1071 }; 0
1072 unsigned Count[] = { 0, 0 }; 0
1073 for (unsigned I = 0; I < 2; ++I) 0
1074 while (RxSBG[I].Input->hasOneUse() && expandRxSBG(RxSBG[I])) 0
1075 // In cases of multiple users it seems better to keep the simple ----
1076 // instruction as they are one cycle faster, and it also helps in cases ----
1077 // where both inputs share a common node. ----
1078 // The widening or narrowing is expected to be free. Counting widening ----
1079 // or narrowing as a saved operation will result in preferring an R*SBG ----
1080 // over a simple shift/logical instruction. ----
1081 if (RxSBG[I].Input.getOpcode() != ISD::ANY_EXTEND && 0
1082 RxSBG[I].Input.getOpcode() != ISD::TRUNCATE) 0
1083 Count[I] += 1; 0
1084 ----
1085 // Do nothing if neither operand is suitable. ----
1086 if (Count[0] == 0 && Count[1] == 0) 0
1087 return false; 0
1088 ----
1089 // Pick the deepest second operand. ----
1090 unsigned I = Count[0] > Count[1] ? 0 : 1; 0
1091 SDValue Op0 = N->getOperand(I ^ 1); 0
1092 ----
1093 // Prefer IC for character insertions from memory. ----
1094 if (Opcode == SystemZ::ROSBG && (RxSBG[I].Mask & 0xff) == 0) 0
1095 if (auto *Load = dyn_cast(Op0.getNode())) 0
1096 if (Load->getMemoryVT() == MVT::i8) 0
1097 return false; 0
1098 ----
1099 // See whether we can avoid an AND in the first operand by converting ----
1100 // ROSBG to RISBG. ----
1101 if (Opcode == SystemZ::ROSBG && detectOrAndInsertion(Op0, RxSBG[I].Mask)) { 0
1102 Opcode = SystemZ::RISBG; 0
1103 // Prefer RISBGN if available, since it does not clobber CC. ----
1104 if (Subtarget->hasMiscellaneousExtensions()) 0
1105 Opcode = SystemZ::RISBGN; 0
1106 } ----
1107 ----
1108 SDValue Ops[5] = { ----
1109 convertTo(DL, MVT::i64, Op0), 0
1110 convertTo(DL, MVT::i64, RxSBG[I].Input), 0
1111 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(RxSBG[I].Start, DL, MVT::i32), 0
1112 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(RxSBG[I].End, DL, MVT::i32), 0
1113 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(RxSBG[I].Rotate, DL, MVT::i32) 0
1114 }; 0
1115 SDValue New = convertTo( 0
1116 DL, VT, SDValue(CurDAG->getMachineNode(Opcode, DL, MVT::i64, Ops), 0)); 0
1117 ReplaceNode(N, New.getNode()); 0
1118 return true; 0
1119 } 0
1120 ----
1121 void SystemZDAGToDAGISel::splitLargeImmediate(unsigned Opcode, SDNode *Node, 0
1122 SDValue Op0, uint64_t UpperVal, ----
1123 uint64_t LowerVal) { ----
1124 EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0); 0
1125 SDLoc DL(Node); 0
1126 SDValue Upper = CurDAG->getConstant(UpperVal, DL, VT); 0
1127 if (Op0.getNode()) 0
1128 Upper = CurDAG->getNode(Opcode, DL, VT, Op0, Upper); 0
1129 ----
1130 { ----
1131 // When we haven't passed in Op0, Upper will be a constant. In order to ----
1132 // prevent folding back to the large immediate in `Or = getNode(...)` we run ----
1133 // SelectCode first and end up with an opaque machine node. This means that ----
1134 // we need to use a handle to keep track of Upper in case it gets CSE'd by ----
1135 // SelectCode. ----
1136 // ----
1137 // Note that in the case where Op0 is passed in we could just call ----
1138 // SelectCode(Upper) later, along with the SelectCode(Or), and avoid needing ----
1139 // the handle at all, but it's fine to do it here. ----
1140 // ----
1141 // TODO: This is a pretty hacky way to do this. Can we do something that ----
1142 // doesn't require a two paragraph explanation? ----
1143 HandleSDNode Handle(Upper); 0
1144 SelectCode(Upper.getNode()); 0
1145 Upper = Handle.getValue(); 0
1146 } 0
1147 ----
1148 SDValue Lower = CurDAG->getConstant(LowerVal, DL, VT); 0
1149 SDValue Or = CurDAG->getNode(Opcode, DL, VT, Upper, Lower); 0
1150 ----
1151 ReplaceNode(Node, Or.getNode()); 0
1152 ----
1153 SelectCode(Or.getNode()); 0
1154 } 0
1155 ----
1156 void SystemZDAGToDAGISel::loadVectorConstant( 0
1157 const SystemZVectorConstantInfo &VCI, SDNode *Node) { ----
1158 assert((VCI.Opcode == SystemZISD::BYTE_MASK || 0
1159 VCI.Opcode == SystemZISD::REPLICATE || ----
1160 VCI.Opcode == SystemZISD::ROTATE_MASK) && ----
1161 "Bad opcode!"); ----
1162 assert(VCI.VecVT.getSizeInBits() == 128 && "Expected a vector type"); 0
1163 EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0); 0
1164 SDLoc DL(Node); 0
1165 SmallVector Ops; 0
1166 for (unsigned OpVal : VCI.OpVals) 0
1167 Ops.push_back(CurDAG->getTargetConstant(OpVal, DL, MVT::i32)); 0
1168 SDValue Op = CurDAG->getNode(VCI.Opcode, DL, VCI.VecVT, Ops); 0
1169 ----
1170 if (VCI.VecVT == VT.getSimpleVT()) 0
1171 ReplaceNode(Node, Op.getNode()); 0
1172 else if (VT.getSizeInBits() == 128) { 0
1173 SDValue BitCast = CurDAG->getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, VT, Op); 0
1174 ReplaceNode(Node, BitCast.getNode()); 0
1175 SelectCode(BitCast.getNode()); 0
1176 } else { // float or double ----
1177 unsigned SubRegIdx = ----
1178 (VT.getSizeInBits() == 32 ? SystemZ::subreg_h32 : SystemZ::subreg_h64); 0
1179 ReplaceNode( 0
1180 Node, CurDAG->getTargetExtractSubreg(SubRegIdx, DL, VT, Op).getNode()); 0
1181 } ----
1182 SelectCode(Op.getNode()); 0
1183 } 0
1184 ----
1185 bool SystemZDAGToDAGISel::tryGather(SDNode *N, unsigned Opcode) { 0
1186 SDValue ElemV = N->getOperand(2); 0
1187 auto *ElemN = dyn_cast(ElemV); 0
1188 if (!ElemN) 0
1189 return false; 0
1190 ----
1191 unsigned Elem = ElemN->getZExtValue(); 0
1192 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0); 0
1193 if (Elem >= VT.getVectorNumElements()) 0
1194 return false; 0
1195 ----
1196 auto *Load = dyn_cast(N->getOperand(1)); 0
1197 if (!Load || !Load->hasNUsesOfValue(1, 0)) 0
1198 return false; 0
1199 if (Load->getMemoryVT().getSizeInBits() != 0
1200 Load->getValueType(0).getSizeInBits()) 0
1201 return false; 0
1202 ----
1203 SDValue Base, Disp, Index; 0
1204 if (!selectBDVAddr12Only(Load->getBasePtr(), ElemV, Base, Disp, Index) || 0
1205 Index.getValueType() != VT.changeVectorElementTypeToInteger()) 0
1206 return false; 0
1207 ----
1208 SDLoc DL(Load); 0
1209 SDValue Ops[] = { ----
1210 N->getOperand(0), Base, Disp, Index, 0
1211 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Elem, DL, MVT::i32), Load->getChain() 0
1212 }; 0
1213 SDNode *Res = CurDAG->getMachineNode(Opcode, DL, VT, MVT::Other, Ops); 0
1214 ReplaceUses(SDValue(Load, 1), SDValue(Res, 1)); 0
1215 ReplaceNode(N, Res); 0
1216 return true; 0
1217 } 0
1218 ----
1219 bool SystemZDAGToDAGISel::tryScatter(StoreSDNode *Store, unsigned Opcode) { 0
1220 SDValue Value = Store->getValue(); 0
1221 if (Value.getOpcode() != ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT) 0
1222 return false; 0
1223 if (Store->getMemoryVT().getSizeInBits() != Value.getValueSizeInBits()) 0
1224 return false; 0
1225 ----
1226 SDValue ElemV = Value.getOperand(1); 0
1227 auto *ElemN = dyn_cast(ElemV); 0
1228 if (!ElemN) 0
1229 return false; 0
1230 ----
1231 SDValue Vec = Value.getOperand(0); 0
1232 EVT VT = Vec.getValueType(); 0
1233 unsigned Elem = ElemN->getZExtValue(); 0
1234 if (Elem >= VT.getVectorNumElements()) 0
1235 return false; 0
1236 ----
1237 SDValue Base, Disp, Index; 0
1238 if (!selectBDVAddr12Only(Store->getBasePtr(), ElemV, Base, Disp, Index) || 0
1239 Index.getValueType() != VT.changeVectorElementTypeToInteger()) 0
1240 return false; 0
1241 ----
1242 SDLoc DL(Store); 0
1243 SDValue Ops[] = { ----
1244 Vec, Base, Disp, Index, CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Elem, DL, MVT::i32), 0
1245 Store->getChain() 0
1246 }; 0
1247 ReplaceNode(Store, CurDAG->getMachineNode(Opcode, DL, MVT::Other, Ops)); 0
1248 return true; 0
1249 } 0
1250 ----
1251 // Check whether or not the chain ending in StoreNode is suitable for doing ----
1252 // the {load; op; store} to modify transformation. ----
1253 static bool isFusableLoadOpStorePattern(StoreSDNode *StoreNode, 0
1254 SDValue StoredVal, SelectionDAG *CurDAG, ----
1255 LoadSDNode *&LoadNode, ----
1256 SDValue &InputChain) { ----
1257 // Is the stored value result 0 of the operation? ----
1258 if (StoredVal.getResNo() != 0) 0
1259 return false; 0
1260 ----
1261 // Are there other uses of the loaded value than the operation? ----
1262 if (!StoredVal.getNode()->hasNUsesOfValue(1, 0)) 0
1263 return false; 0
1264 ----
1265 // Is the store non-extending and non-indexed? ----
1266 if (!ISD::isNormalStore(StoreNode) || StoreNode->isNonTemporal()) 0
1267 return false; 0
1268 ----
1269 SDValue Load = StoredVal->getOperand(0); 0
1270 // Is the stored value a non-extending and non-indexed load? ----
1271 if (!ISD::isNormalLoad(Load.getNode())) 0
1272 return false; 0
1273 ----
1274 // Return LoadNode by reference. ----
1275 LoadNode = cast(Load); 0
1276 ----
1277 // Is store the only read of the loaded value? ----
1278 if (!Load.hasOneUse()) 0
1279 return false; 0
1280 ----
1281 // Is the address of the store the same as the load? ----
1282 if (LoadNode->getBasePtr() != StoreNode->getBasePtr() || 0
1283 LoadNode->getOffset() != StoreNode->getOffset()) 0
1284 return false; 0
1285 ----
1286 // Check if the chain is produced by the load or is a TokenFactor with ----
1287 // the load output chain as an operand. Return InputChain by reference. ----
1288 SDValue Chain = StoreNode->getChain(); 0
1289 ----
1290 bool ChainCheck = false; 0
1291 if (Chain == Load.getValue(1)) { 0
1292 ChainCheck = true; 0
1293 InputChain = LoadNode->getChain(); 0
1294 } else if (Chain.getOpcode() == ISD::TokenFactor) { 0
1295 SmallVector ChainOps; 0
1296 SmallVector LoopWorklist; 0
1297 SmallPtrSet Visited; 0
1298 const unsigned int Max = 1024; 0
1299 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Chain.getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) { 0
1300 SDValue Op = Chain.getOperand(i); 0
1301 if (Op == Load.getValue(1)) { 0
1302 ChainCheck = true; 0
1303 // Drop Load, but keep its chain. No cycle check necessary. ----
1304 ChainOps.push_back(Load.getOperand(0)); 0
1305 continue; 0
1306 } ----
1307 LoopWorklist.push_back(Op.getNode()); 0
1308 ChainOps.push_back(Op); 0
1309 } ----
1310 ----
1311 if (ChainCheck) { 0
1312 // Add the other operand of StoredVal to worklist. ----
1313 for (SDValue Op : StoredVal->ops()) 0
1314 if (Op.getNode() != LoadNode) 0
1315 LoopWorklist.push_back(Op.getNode()); 0
1316 ----
1317 // Check if Load is reachable from any of the nodes in the worklist. ----
1318 if (SDNode::hasPredecessorHelper(Load.getNode(), Visited, LoopWorklist, Max, 0
1319 true)) ----
1320 return false; 0
1321 ----
1322 // Make a new TokenFactor with all the other input chains except ----
1323 // for the load. ----
1324 InputChain = CurDAG->getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, SDLoc(Chain), 0
1325 MVT::Other, ChainOps); ----
1326 } ----
1327 } 0
1328 if (!ChainCheck) 0
1329 return false; 0
1330 ----
1331 return true; 0
1332 } ----
1333 ----
1334 // Change a chain of {load; op; store} of the same value into a simple op ----
1335 // through memory of that value, if the uses of the modified value and its ----
1336 // address are suitable. ----
1337 // ----
1338 // The tablegen pattern memory operand pattern is currently not able to match ----
1339 // the case where the CC on the original operation are used. ----
1340 // ----
1341 // See the equivalent routine in X86ISelDAGToDAG for further comments. ----
1342 bool SystemZDAGToDAGISel::tryFoldLoadStoreIntoMemOperand(SDNode *Node) { 0
1343 StoreSDNode *StoreNode = cast(Node); 0
1344 SDValue StoredVal = StoreNode->getOperand(1); 0
1345 unsigned Opc = StoredVal->getOpcode(); 0
1346 SDLoc DL(StoreNode); 0
1347 ----
1348 // Before we try to select anything, make sure this is memory operand size ----
1349 // and opcode we can handle. Note that this must match the code below that ----
1350 // actually lowers the opcodes. ----
1351 EVT MemVT = StoreNode->getMemoryVT(); 0
1352 unsigned NewOpc = 0; 0
1353 bool NegateOperand = false; 0
1354 switch (Opc) { 0
1355 default: 0
1356 return false; 0
1357 case SystemZISD::SSUBO: 0
1358 NegateOperand = true; 0
1359 [[fallthrough]]; ----
1360 case SystemZISD::SADDO: 0
1361 if (MemVT == MVT::i32) 0
1362 NewOpc = SystemZ::ASI; 0
1363 else if (MemVT == MVT::i64) 0
1364 NewOpc = SystemZ::AGSI; 0
1365 else ----
1366 return false; 0
1367 break; 0
1368 case SystemZISD::USUBO: 0
1369 NegateOperand = true; 0
1370 [[fallthrough]]; ----
1371 case SystemZISD::UADDO: 0
1372 if (MemVT == MVT::i32) 0
1373 NewOpc = SystemZ::ALSI; 0
1374 else if (MemVT == MVT::i64) 0
1375 NewOpc = SystemZ::ALGSI; 0
1376 else ----
1377 return false; 0
1378 break; 0
1379 } ----
1380 ----
1381 LoadSDNode *LoadNode = nullptr; 0
1382 SDValue InputChain; 0
1383 if (!isFusableLoadOpStorePattern(StoreNode, StoredVal, CurDAG, LoadNode, 0
1384 InputChain)) ----
1385 return false; 0
1386 ----
1387 SDValue Operand = StoredVal.getOperand(1); 0
1388 auto *OperandC = dyn_cast(Operand); 0
1389 if (!OperandC) 0
1390 return false; 0
1391 auto OperandV = OperandC->getAPIntValue(); 0
1392 if (NegateOperand) 0
1393 OperandV = -OperandV; 0
1394 if (OperandV.getSignificantBits() > 8) 0
1395 return false; 0
1396 Operand = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(OperandV, DL, MemVT); 0
1397 ----
1398 SDValue Base, Disp; 0
1399 if (!selectBDAddr20Only(StoreNode->getBasePtr(), Base, Disp)) 0
1400 return false; 0
1401 ----
1402 SDValue Ops[] = { Base, Disp, Operand, InputChain }; 0
1403 MachineSDNode *Result = ----
1404 CurDAG->getMachineNode(NewOpc, DL, MVT::i32, MVT::Other, Ops); 0
1405 CurDAG->setNodeMemRefs( 0
1406 Result, {StoreNode->getMemOperand(), LoadNode->getMemOperand()}); 0
1407 ----
1408 ReplaceUses(SDValue(StoreNode, 0), SDValue(Result, 1)); 0
1409 ReplaceUses(SDValue(StoredVal.getNode(), 1), SDValue(Result, 0)); 0
1410 CurDAG->RemoveDeadNode(Node); 0
1411 return true; 0
1412 } 0
1413 ----
1414 bool SystemZDAGToDAGISel::canUseBlockOperation(StoreSDNode *Store, 0
1415 LoadSDNode *Load) const { ----
1416 // Check that the two memory operands have the same size. ----
1417 if (Load->getMemoryVT() != Store->getMemoryVT()) 0
1418 return false; 0
1419 ----
1420 // Volatility stops an access from being decomposed. ----
1421 if (Load->isVolatile() || Store->isVolatile()) 0
1422 return false; 0
1423 ----
1424 // There's no chance of overlap if the load is invariant. ----
1425 if (Load->isInvariant() && Load->isDereferenceable()) 0
1426 return true; 0
1427 ----
1428 // Otherwise we need to check whether there's an alias. ----
1429 const Value *V1 = Load->getMemOperand()->getValue(); 0
1430 const Value *V2 = Store->getMemOperand()->getValue(); 0
1431 if (!V1 || !V2) 0
1432 return false; 0
1433 ----
1434 // Reject equality. ----
1435 uint64_t Size = Load->getMemoryVT().getStoreSize(); 0
1436 int64_t End1 = Load->getSrcValueOffset() + Size; 0
1437 int64_t End2 = Store->getSrcValueOffset() + Size; 0
1438 if (V1 == V2 && End1 == End2) 0
1439 return false; 0
1440 ----
1441 return AA->isNoAlias(MemoryLocation(V1, End1, Load->getAAInfo()), 0
1442 MemoryLocation(V2, End2, Store->getAAInfo())); 0
1443 } ----
1444 ----
1445 bool SystemZDAGToDAGISel::storeLoadCanUseMVC(SDNode *N) const { 0
1446 auto *Store = cast(N); 0
1447 auto *Load = cast(Store->getValue()); 0
1448 ----
1449 // Prefer not to use MVC if either address can use ... RELATIVE LONG ----
1450 // instructions. ----
1451 uint64_t Size = Load->getMemoryVT().getStoreSize(); 0
1452 if (Size > 1 && Size <= 8) { 0
1453 // Prefer LHRL, LRL and LGRL. ----
1454 if (SystemZISD::isPCREL(Load->getBasePtr().getOpcode())) 0
1455 return false; 0
1456 // Prefer STHRL, STRL and STGRL. ----
1457 if (SystemZISD::isPCREL(Store->getBasePtr().getOpcode())) 0
1458 return false; 0
1459 } ----
1460 ----
1461 return canUseBlockOperation(Store, Load); 0
1462 } ----
1463 ----
1464 bool SystemZDAGToDAGISel::storeLoadCanUseBlockBinary(SDNode *N, 0
1465 unsigned I) const { ----
1466 auto *StoreA = cast(N); 0
1467 auto *LoadA = cast(StoreA->getValue().getOperand(1 - I)); 0
1468 auto *LoadB = cast(StoreA->getValue().getOperand(I)); 0
1469 return !LoadA->isVolatile() && LoadA->getMemoryVT() == LoadB->getMemoryVT() && 0
1470 canUseBlockOperation(StoreA, LoadB); 0
1471 } ----
1472 ----
1473 bool SystemZDAGToDAGISel::storeLoadIsAligned(SDNode *N) const { 0
1474 ----
1475 auto *MemAccess = cast(N); 0
1476 TypeSize StoreSize = MemAccess->getMemoryVT().getStoreSize(); 0
1477 SDValue BasePtr = MemAccess->getBasePtr(); 0
1478 MachineMemOperand *MMO = MemAccess->getMemOperand(); 0
1479 assert(MMO && "Expected a memory operand."); 0
1480 ----
1481 // The memory access must have a proper alignment and no index register. ----
1482 if (MemAccess->getAlign().value() < StoreSize || 0
1483 !MemAccess->getOffset().isUndef()) 0
1484 return false; 0
1485 ----
1486 // The MMO must not have an unaligned offset. ----
1487 if (MMO->getOffset() % StoreSize != 0) 0
1488 return false; 0
1489 ----
1490 // An access to GOT or the Constant Pool is aligned. ----
1491 if (const PseudoSourceValue *PSV = MMO->getPseudoValue()) 0
1492 if ((PSV->isGOT() || PSV->isConstantPool())) 0
1493 return true; 0
1494 ----
1495 // Check the alignment of a Global Address. ----
1496 if (BasePtr.getNumOperands()) 0
1497 if (GlobalAddressSDNode *GA = 0
1498 dyn_cast(BasePtr.getOperand(0))) { 0
1499 // The immediate offset must be aligned. ----
1500 if (GA->getOffset() % StoreSize != 0) 0
1501 return false; 0
1502 ----
1503 // The alignment of the symbol itself must be at least the store size. ----
1504 const GlobalValue *GV = GA->getGlobal(); 0
1505 const DataLayout &DL = GV->getParent()->getDataLayout(); 0
1506 if (GV->getPointerAlignment(DL).value() < StoreSize) 0
1507 return false; 0
1508 } ----
1509 ----
1510 return true; 0
1511 } ----
1512 ----
1513 void SystemZDAGToDAGISel::Select(SDNode *Node) { 0
1514 // If we have a custom node, we already have selected! ----
1515 if (Node->isMachineOpcode()) { 0
1516 LLVM_DEBUG(errs() << "== "; Node->dump(CurDAG); errs() << "\n"); 0
1517 Node->setNodeId(-1); 0
1518 return; 0
1519 } ----
1520 ----
1521 unsigned Opcode = Node->getOpcode(); 0
1522 switch (Opcode) { 0
1523 case ISD::OR: 0
1524 if (Node->getOperand(1).getOpcode() != ISD::Constant) 0
1525 if (tryRxSBG(Node, SystemZ::ROSBG)) 0
1526 return; 0
1527 goto or_xor; 0
1528 ----
1529 case ISD::XOR: 0
1530 if (Node->getOperand(1).getOpcode() != ISD::Constant) 0
1531 if (tryRxSBG(Node, SystemZ::RXSBG)) 0
1532 return; 0
1533 // Fall through. ----
1534 or_xor: 0
1535 // If this is a 64-bit operation in which both 32-bit halves are nonzero, ----
1536 // split the operation into two. If both operands here happen to be ----
1537 // constant, leave this to common code to optimize. ----
1538 if (Node->getValueType(0) == MVT::i64 && 0
1539 Node->getOperand(0).getOpcode() != ISD::Constant) 0
1540 if (auto *Op1 = dyn_cast(Node->getOperand(1))) { 0
1541 uint64_t Val = Op1->getZExtValue(); 0
1542 // Don't split the operation if we can match one of the combined ----
1543 // logical operations provided by miscellaneous-extensions-3. ----
1544 if (Subtarget->hasMiscellaneousExtensions3()) { 0
1545 unsigned ChildOpcode = Node->getOperand(0).getOpcode(); 0
1546 // Check whether this expression matches NAND/NOR/NXOR. ----
1547 if (Val == (uint64_t)-1 && Opcode == ISD::XOR) 0
1548 if (ChildOpcode == ISD::AND || ChildOpcode == ISD::OR || 0
1549 ChildOpcode == ISD::XOR) ----
1550 break; ----
1551 // Check whether this expression matches OR-with-complement ----
1552 // (or matches an alternate pattern for NXOR). ----
1553 if (ChildOpcode == ISD::XOR) { 0
1554 auto Op0 = Node->getOperand(0); 0
1555 if (auto *Op0Op1 = dyn_cast(Op0->getOperand(1))) 0
1556 if (Op0Op1->getZExtValue() == (uint64_t)-1) 0
1557 break; 0
1558 } ----
1559 } ----
1560 if (!SystemZ::isImmLF(Val) && !SystemZ::isImmHF(Val)) { 0
1561 splitLargeImmediate(Opcode, Node, Node->getOperand(0), 0
1562 Val - uint32_t(Val), uint32_t(Val)); 0
1563 return; 0
1564 } ----
1565 } ----
1566 break; 0
1567 ----
1568 case ISD::AND: 0
1569 if (Node->getOperand(1).getOpcode() != ISD::Constant) 0
1570 if (tryRxSBG(Node, SystemZ::RNSBG)) 0
1571 return; 0
1572 [[fallthrough]]; ----
1573 case ISD::ROTL: ----
1574 case ISD::SHL: ----
1575 case ISD::SRL: ----
1576 case ISD::ZERO_EXTEND: ----
1577 if (tryRISBGZero(Node)) 0
1578 return; 0
1579 break; 0
1580 ----
1581 case ISD::Constant: 0
1582 // If this is a 64-bit constant that is out of the range of LLILF, ----
1583 // LLIHF and LGFI, split it into two 32-bit pieces. ----
1584 if (Node->getValueType(0) == MVT::i64) { 0
1585 uint64_t Val = cast(Node)->getZExtValue(); 0
1586 if (!SystemZ::isImmLF(Val) && !SystemZ::isImmHF(Val) && !isInt<32>(Val)) { 0
1587 splitLargeImmediate(ISD::OR, Node, SDValue(), Val - uint32_t(Val), 0
1588 uint32_t(Val)); ----
1589 return; 0
1590 } ----
1591 } ----
1592 break; 0
1593 ----
1594 case SystemZISD::SELECT_CCMASK: { 0
1595 SDValue Op0 = Node->getOperand(0); 0
1596 SDValue Op1 = Node->getOperand(1); 0
1597 // Prefer to put any load first, so that it can be matched as a ----
1598 // conditional load. Likewise for constants in range for LOCHI. ----
1599 if ((Op1.getOpcode() == ISD::LOAD && Op0.getOpcode() != ISD::LOAD) || 0
1600 (Subtarget->hasLoadStoreOnCond2() && 0
1601 Node->getValueType(0).isInteger() && 0
1602 Op1.getOpcode() == ISD::Constant && 0
1603 isInt<16>(cast(Op1)->getSExtValue()) && 0
1604 !(Op0.getOpcode() == ISD::Constant && 0
1605 isInt<16>(cast(Op0)->getSExtValue())))) { 0
1606 SDValue CCValid = Node->getOperand(2); 0
1607 SDValue CCMask = Node->getOperand(3); 0
1608 uint64_t ConstCCValid = ----
1609 cast(CCValid.getNode())->getZExtValue(); 0
1610 uint64_t ConstCCMask = ----
1611 cast(CCMask.getNode())->getZExtValue(); 0
1612 // Invert the condition. ----
1613 CCMask = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(ConstCCValid ^ ConstCCMask, 0
1614 SDLoc(Node), CCMask.getValueType()); 0
1615 SDValue Op4 = Node->getOperand(4); 0
1616 SDNode *UpdatedNode = ----
1617 CurDAG->UpdateNodeOperands(Node, Op1, Op0, CCValid, CCMask, Op4); 0
1618 if (UpdatedNode != Node) { 0
1619 // In case this node already exists then replace Node with it. ----
1620 ReplaceNode(Node, UpdatedNode); 0
1621 Node = UpdatedNode; 0
1622 } ----
1623 } ----
1624 break; 0
1625 } ----
1626 ----
1627 case ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT: { 0
1628 EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0); 0
1629 unsigned ElemBitSize = VT.getScalarSizeInBits(); 0
1630 if (ElemBitSize == 32) { 0
1631 if (tryGather(Node, SystemZ::VGEF)) 0
1632 return; 0
1633 } else if (ElemBitSize == 64) { 0
1634 if (tryGather(Node, SystemZ::VGEG)) 0
1635 return; 0
1636 } ----
1637 break; 0
1638 } ----
1639 ----
1640 case ISD::BUILD_VECTOR: { 0
1641 auto *BVN = cast(Node); 0
1642 SystemZVectorConstantInfo VCI(BVN); 0
1643 if (VCI.isVectorConstantLegal(*Subtarget)) { 0
1644 loadVectorConstant(VCI, Node); 0
1645 return; 0
1646 } ----
1647 break; 0
1648 } 0
1649 ----
1650 case ISD::ConstantFP: { 0
1651 APFloat Imm = cast(Node)->getValueAPF(); 0
1652 if (Imm.isZero() || Imm.isNegZero()) 0
1653 break; 0
1654 SystemZVectorConstantInfo VCI(Imm); 0
1655 bool Success = VCI.isVectorConstantLegal(*Subtarget); (void)Success; 0
1656 assert(Success && "Expected legal FP immediate"); 0
1657 loadVectorConstant(VCI, Node); 0
1658 return; 0
1659 } 0
1660 ----
1661 case ISD::STORE: { 0
1662 if (tryFoldLoadStoreIntoMemOperand(Node)) 0
1663 return; 0
1664 auto *Store = cast(Node); 0
1665 unsigned ElemBitSize = Store->getValue().getValueSizeInBits(); 0
1666 if (ElemBitSize == 32) { 0
1667 if (tryScatter(Store, SystemZ::VSCEF)) 0
1668 return; 0
1669 } else if (ElemBitSize == 64) { 0
1670 if (tryScatter(Store, SystemZ::VSCEG)) 0
1671 return; 0
1672 } ----
1673 break; 0
1674 } ----
1675 } ----
1676 ----
1677 SelectCode(Node); 0
1678 } ----
1679 ----
1680 bool SystemZDAGToDAGISel:: 0
1681 SelectInlineAsmMemoryOperand(const SDValue &Op, ----
1682 unsigned ConstraintID, ----
1683 std::vector &OutOps) { ----
1684 SystemZAddressingMode::AddrForm Form; ----
1685 SystemZAddressingMode::DispRange DispRange; ----
1686 SDValue Base, Disp, Index; 0
1687 ----
1688 switch(ConstraintID) { 0
1689 default: 0
1690 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected asm memory constraint"); 0
1691 case InlineAsm::Constraint_i: 0
1692 case InlineAsm::Constraint_Q: ----
1693 case InlineAsm::Constraint_ZQ: ----
1694 // Accept an address with a short displacement, but no index. ----
1695 Form = SystemZAddressingMode::FormBD; 0
1696 DispRange = SystemZAddressingMode::Disp12Only; 0
1697 break; 0
1698 case InlineAsm::Constraint_R: 0
1699 case InlineAsm::Constraint_ZR: ----
1700 // Accept an address with a short displacement and an index. ----
1701 Form = SystemZAddressingMode::FormBDXNormal; 0
1702 DispRange = SystemZAddressingMode::Disp12Only; 0
1703 break; 0
1704 case InlineAsm::Constraint_S: 0
1705 case InlineAsm::Constraint_ZS: ----
1706 // Accept an address with a long displacement, but no index. ----
1707 Form = SystemZAddressingMode::FormBD; 0
1708 DispRange = SystemZAddressingMode::Disp20Only; 0
1709 break; 0
1710 case InlineAsm::Constraint_T: 0
1711 case InlineAsm::Constraint_m: ----
1712 case InlineAsm::Constraint_o: ----
1713 case InlineAsm::Constraint_p: ----
1714 case InlineAsm::Constraint_ZT: ----
1715 // Accept an address with a long displacement and an index. ----
1716 // m works the same as T, as this is the most general case. ----
1717 // We don't really have any special handling of "offsettable" ----
1718 // memory addresses, so just treat o the same as m. ----
1719 Form = SystemZAddressingMode::FormBDXNormal; 0
1720 DispRange = SystemZAddressingMode::Disp20Only; 0
1721 break; 0
1722 } ----
1723 ----
1724 if (selectBDXAddr(Form, DispRange, Op, Base, Disp, Index)) { 0
1725 const TargetRegisterClass *TRC = ----
1726 Subtarget->getRegisterInfo()->getPointerRegClass(*MF); 0
1727 SDLoc DL(Base); 0
1728 SDValue RC = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(TRC->getID(), DL, MVT::i32); 0
1729 ----
1730 // Make sure that the base address doesn't go into %r0. ----
1731 // If it's a TargetFrameIndex or a fixed register, we shouldn't do anything. ----
1732 if (Base.getOpcode() != ISD::TargetFrameIndex && 0
1733 Base.getOpcode() != ISD::Register) { 0
1734 Base = 0
1735 SDValue(CurDAG->getMachineNode(TargetOpcode::COPY_TO_REGCLASS, 0
1736 DL, Base.getValueType(), ----
1737 Base, RC), 0); ----
1738 } ----
1739 ----
1740 // Make sure that the index register isn't assigned to %r0 either. ----
1741 if (Index.getOpcode() != ISD::Register) { 0
1742 Index = 0
1743 SDValue(CurDAG->getMachineNode(TargetOpcode::COPY_TO_REGCLASS, 0
1744 DL, Index.getValueType(), ----
1745 Index, RC), 0); ----
1746 } ----
1747 ----
1748 OutOps.push_back(Base); 0
1749 OutOps.push_back(Disp); 0
1750 OutOps.push_back(Index); 0
1751 return false; 0
1752 } 0
1753 ----
1754 return true; 0
1755 } ----

1757 // IsProfitableToFold - Returns true if is profitable to fold the specific ----
1758 // operand node N of U during instruction selection that starts at Root. ----
1759 bool ----
1760 SystemZDAGToDAGISel::IsProfitableToFold(SDValue N, SDNode *U, 0
1761 SDNode *Root) const { ----
1762 // We want to avoid folding a LOAD into an ICMP node if as a result ----
1763 // we would be forced to spill the condition code into a GPR. ----
1764 if (N.getOpcode() == ISD::LOAD && U->getOpcode() == SystemZISD::ICMP) { 0
1765 if (!N.hasOneUse() || !U->hasOneUse()) 0
1766 return false; 0
1767 ----
1768 // The user of the CC value will usually be a CopyToReg into the ----
1769 // physical CC register, which in turn is glued and chained to the ----
1770 // actual instruction that uses the CC value. Bail out if we have ----
1771 // anything else than that. ----
1772 SDNode *CCUser = *U->use_begin(); 0
1773 SDNode *CCRegUser = nullptr; 0
1774 if (CCUser->getOpcode() == ISD::CopyToReg || 0
1775 cast(CCUser->getOperand(1))->getReg() == SystemZ::CC) { 0
1776 for (auto *U : CCUser->uses()) { 0
1777 if (CCRegUser == nullptr) 0
1778 CCRegUser = U; 0
1779 else if (CCRegUser != U) 0
1780 return false; 0
1781 } ----
1782 } ----
1783 if (CCRegUser == nullptr) 0
1784 return false; 0
1785 ----
1786 // If the actual instruction is a branch, the only thing that remains to be ----
1787 // checked is whether the CCUser chain is a predecessor of the load. ----
1788 if (CCRegUser->isMachineOpcode() && 0
1789 CCRegUser->getMachineOpcode() == SystemZ::BRC) 0
1790 return !N->isPredecessorOf(CCUser->getOperand(0).getNode()); 0
1791 ----
1792 // Otherwise, the instruction may have multiple operands, and we need to ----
1793 // verify that none of them are a predecessor of the load. This is exactly ----
1794 // the same check that would be done by common code if the CC setter were ----
1795 // glued to the CC user, so simply invoke that check here. ----
1796 if (!IsLegalToFold(N, U, CCRegUser, OptLevel, false)) 0
1797 return false; 0
1798 } ----
1799 ----
1800 return true; 0
1801 } ----

1803 namespace { ----
1804 // Represents a sequence for extracting a 0/1 value from an IPM result: ----
1805 // (((X ^ XORValue) + AddValue) >> Bit) ----
1806 struct IPMConversion { ----
1807 IPMConversion(unsigned xorValue, int64_t addValue, unsigned bit) 0
1808 : XORValue(xorValue), AddValue(addValue), Bit(bit) {} 0
1809 ----
1810 int64_t XORValue; ----
1811 int64_t AddValue; ----
1812 unsigned Bit; ----
1813 }; ----
1814 } // end anonymous namespace ----
1815 ----
1816 // Return a sequence for getting a 1 from an IPM result when CC has a ----
1817 // value in CCMask and a 0 when CC has a value in CCValid & ~CCMask. ----
1818 // The handling of CC values outside CCValid doesn't matter. ----
1819 static IPMConversion getIPMConversion(unsigned CCValid, unsigned CCMask) { 0
1820 // Deal with cases where the result can be taken directly from a bit ----
1821 // of the IPM result. ----
1822 if (CCMask == (CCValid & (SystemZ::CCMASK_1 | SystemZ::CCMASK_3))) 0
1823 return IPMConversion(0, 0, SystemZ::IPM_CC); 0
1824 if (CCMask == (CCValid & (SystemZ::CCMASK_2 | SystemZ::CCMASK_3))) 0
1825 return IPMConversion(0, 0, SystemZ::IPM_CC + 1); 0
1826 ----
1827 // Deal with cases where we can add a value to force the sign bit ----
1828 // to contain the right value. Putting the bit in 31 means we can ----
1829 // use SRL rather than RISBG(L), and also makes it easier to get a ----
1830 // 0/-1 value, so it has priority over the other tests below. ----
1831 // ----
1832 // These sequences rely on the fact that the upper two bits of the ----
1833 // IPM result are zero. ----
1834 uint64_t TopBit = uint64_t(1) << 31; 0
1835 if (CCMask == (CCValid & SystemZ::CCMASK_0)) 0
1836 return IPMConversion(0, -(1 << SystemZ::IPM_CC), 31); 0
1837 if (CCMask == (CCValid & (SystemZ::CCMASK_0 | SystemZ::CCMASK_1))) 0
1838 return IPMConversion(0, -(2 << SystemZ::IPM_CC), 31); 0
1839 if (CCMask == (CCValid & (SystemZ::CCMASK_0 0
1840 | SystemZ::CCMASK_1 ----
1841 | SystemZ::CCMASK_2))) ----
1842 return IPMConversion(0, -(3 << SystemZ::IPM_CC), 31); 0
1843 if (CCMask == (CCValid & SystemZ::CCMASK_3)) 0
1844 return IPMConversion(0, TopBit - (3 << SystemZ::IPM_CC), 31); 0
1845 if (CCMask == (CCValid & (SystemZ::CCMASK_1 0
1846 | SystemZ::CCMASK_2 ----
1847 | SystemZ::CCMASK_3))) ----
1848 return IPMConversion(0, TopBit - (1 << SystemZ::IPM_CC), 31); 0
1849 ----
1850 // Next try inverting the value and testing a bit. 0/1 could be ----
1851 // handled this way too, but we dealt with that case above. ----
1852 if (CCMask == (CCValid & (SystemZ::CCMASK_0 | SystemZ::CCMASK_2))) 0
1853 return IPMConversion(-1, 0, SystemZ::IPM_CC); 0
1854 ----
1855 // Handle cases where adding a value forces a non-sign bit to contain ----
1856 // the right value. ----
1857 if (CCMask == (CCValid & (SystemZ::CCMASK_1 | SystemZ::CCMASK_2))) 0
1858 return IPMConversion(0, 1 << SystemZ::IPM_CC, SystemZ::IPM_CC + 1); 0
1859 if (CCMask == (CCValid & (SystemZ::CCMASK_0 | SystemZ::CCMASK_3))) 0
1860 return IPMConversion(0, -(1 << SystemZ::IPM_CC), SystemZ::IPM_CC + 1); 0
1861 ----
1862 // The remaining cases are 1, 2, 0/1/3 and 0/2/3. All these are ----
1863 // can be done by inverting the low CC bit and applying one of the ----
1864 // sign-based extractions above. ----
1865 if (CCMask == (CCValid & SystemZ::CCMASK_1)) 0
1866 return IPMConversion(1 << SystemZ::IPM_CC, -(1 << SystemZ::IPM_CC), 31); 0
1867 if (CCMask == (CCValid & SystemZ::CCMASK_2)) 0
1868 return IPMConversion(1 << SystemZ::IPM_CC, ----
1869 TopBit - (3 << SystemZ::IPM_CC), 31); 0
1870 if (CCMask == (CCValid & (SystemZ::CCMASK_0 0
1871 | SystemZ::CCMASK_1 ----
1872 | SystemZ::CCMASK_3))) ----
1873 return IPMConversion(1 << SystemZ::IPM_CC, -(3 << SystemZ::IPM_CC), 31); 0
1874 if (CCMask == (CCValid & (SystemZ::CCMASK_0 0
1875 | SystemZ::CCMASK_2 ----
1876 | SystemZ::CCMASK_3))) ----
1877 return IPMConversion(1 << SystemZ::IPM_CC, ----
1878 TopBit - (1 << SystemZ::IPM_CC), 31); 0
1879 ----
1880 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected CC combination"); 0
1881 } ----
1882 ----
1883 SDValue SystemZDAGToDAGISel::expandSelectBoolean(SDNode *Node) { 0
1884 auto *TrueOp = dyn_cast(Node->getOperand(0)); 0
1885 auto *FalseOp = dyn_cast(Node->getOperand(1)); 0
1886 if (!TrueOp || !FalseOp) 0
1887 return SDValue(); 0
1888 if (FalseOp->getZExtValue() != 0) 0
1889 return SDValue(); 0
1890 if (TrueOp->getSExtValue() != 1 && TrueOp->getSExtValue() != -1) 0
1891 return SDValue(); 0
1892 ----
1893 auto *CCValidOp = dyn_cast(Node->getOperand(2)); 0
1894 auto *CCMaskOp = dyn_cast(Node->getOperand(3)); 0
1895 if (!CCValidOp || !CCMaskOp) 0
1896 return SDValue(); 0
1897 int CCValid = CCValidOp->getZExtValue(); 0
1898 int CCMask = CCMaskOp->getZExtValue(); 0
1899 ----
1900 SDLoc DL(Node); 0
1901 SDValue CCReg = Node->getOperand(4); 0
1902 IPMConversion IPM = getIPMConversion(CCValid, CCMask); 0
1903 SDValue Result = CurDAG->getNode(SystemZISD::IPM, DL, MVT::i32, CCReg); 0
1904 ----
1905 if (IPM.XORValue) 0
1906 Result = CurDAG->getNode(ISD::XOR, DL, MVT::i32, Result, 0
1907 CurDAG->getConstant(IPM.XORValue, DL, MVT::i32)); 0
1908 ----
1909 if (IPM.AddValue) 0
1910 Result = CurDAG->getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, MVT::i32, Result, 0
1911 CurDAG->getConstant(IPM.AddValue, DL, MVT::i32)); 0
1912 ----
1913 EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0); 0
1914 if (VT == MVT::i32 && IPM.Bit == 31) { 0
1915 unsigned ShiftOp = TrueOp->getSExtValue() == 1 ? ISD::SRL : ISD::SRA; 0
1916 Result = CurDAG->getNode(ShiftOp, DL, MVT::i32, Result, 0
1917 CurDAG->getConstant(IPM.Bit, DL, MVT::i32)); 0
1918 } else { ----
1919 if (VT != MVT::i32) 0
1920 Result = CurDAG->getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, DL, VT, Result); 0
1921 ----
1922 if (TrueOp->getSExtValue() == 1) { 0
1923 // The SHR/AND sequence should get optimized to an RISBG. ----
1924 Result = CurDAG->getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, VT, Result, 0
1925 CurDAG->getConstant(IPM.Bit, DL, MVT::i32)); 0
1926 Result = CurDAG->getNode(ISD::AND, DL, VT, Result, 0
1927 CurDAG->getConstant(1, DL, VT)); 0
1928 } else { ----
1929 // Sign-extend from IPM.Bit using a pair of shifts. ----
1930 int ShlAmt = VT.getSizeInBits() - 1 - IPM.Bit; 0
1931 int SraAmt = VT.getSizeInBits() - 1; 0
1932 Result = CurDAG->getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, VT, Result, 0
1933 CurDAG->getConstant(ShlAmt, DL, MVT::i32)); 0
1934 Result = CurDAG->getNode(ISD::SRA, DL, VT, Result, 0
1935 CurDAG->getConstant(SraAmt, DL, MVT::i32)); 0
1936 } ----
1937 } ----
1938 ----
1939 return Result; 0
1940 } 0

1944 // using those over an IPM sequence. ----

1947 ----

1949 ----

1955 continue; 0

1968 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\nNew: "); 0

1970 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\n"); 0
1971 ----
1972 CurDAG->ReplaceAllUsesOfValueWith(SDValue(N, 0), Res); 0
1973 MadeChange = true; 0
1974 } ----
1975 } ----
1976 ----
1977 if (MadeChange) 0
1978 CurDAG->RemoveDeadNodes(); 0
1979 } ----
